# GitHub Token for accessing GitHub Models API
# 
# This token is required to authenticate with GitHub's Models API service
# which provides access to OpenAI's GPT-4o model through GitHub's infrastructure.
#
# How to get your GitHub token:
# 1. Go to: https://github.com/settings/tokens
# 2. Click "Generate new token" â†’ "Generate new token (classic)"
# 3. Give it a descriptive name like "Persona AI Chat App"
# 4. Select appropriate scopes (ensure access to GitHub Models)
# 5. Copy the generated token and paste it below
#
# Note: Keep this token secure and never commit it to version control
# Multiple tokens can be provided separated by commas for load balancing
#
GITHUB_TOKEN=your_github_token_here

# Optional: Site URL for GitHub Models API headers (for development)
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=http://localhost:3000
